    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Instead of spell slots, you use essence to cast your spells, either through an incantation or through drawing and building up essence throughout a battle.</p><p>When using essence casting, you have a number of prepared spells or a spell repertoire as normal. However, you don’t spend spell slots to cast spells. Instead, you can cast spells from your prepared spells or repertoire only when you have essence equal to or greater than the spell’s rank, or via incantations. You cast focus spells and cantrips the same as normal, and they don’t require essence. Certain cantrips, called draw cantrips, can help you gain essence. Spells that normally require spell slots are called “essence spells” in this system of spellcasting.</p>",
      "gm": ""
    },
